ssary-title"><a href="/glossary/cheddar">Cheddar</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">Ched-ah</span><p>Once cheddar was 'Cheddar', a large, hard-pressed barrel of cheese made by a particular…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 x 160g cans tuna steakin spring water, drained">2 x 160g cans tuna steak in spring water, drained</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="330g can sweetcorn, drained">330g can <a href="/glossary/sweetcorn" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--4 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">sweetcorn</a>, drained<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--4"><article id="node-252341" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/sweetcorn"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/sweetcorn.jpg?itok=-1CXLCu7" width="100" height="100" alt="Sweetcorn" title="Also known as corn on the cob, sweetcorn is composed of rows of tightly packed golden yellow kernels, growing along a tough central core" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/sweetcorn">Sweetcorn</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">sw-eet corn</span><p>Also known as corn on the cob, sweetcorn is composed of rows of tightly packed golden yellow…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="large handful chopped parsley">large handful chopped <a href="/glossary/parsley" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--5 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">parsley</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-gl